{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix DCI allocation indexing bug in pdcchsim\n\n### Summary\nThe `get_dci()` function in pdcchsim.c had a critical bug where multiple DCI formats would overwrite each other in the output array. This happened because the same index was used for both reading input formats and writing to the output allocation array.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/SIMULATION/LTE_PHY/pdcchsim.c`: Added separate output index tracking to prevent overwrites\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen running PDCCH simulations with multiple DCI formats specified (e.g., both format1A and format1), only the last format would be present in the output DCI_PDU structure. Earlier formats would be silently overwritten, leading to missing DCI allocations in the simulation results.\n\nUsers can reproduce this by running pdcchsim with multiple format selectors and observing that only the last format appears in the generated DCI PDU, even though multiple formats were requested.\n\n"
}